events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — LeBron James has been pleading for weeks for the Lakers' supporting cast to provide him and fellow All-Star Anthony Davis some help as they fight to keep pace in a tight Western Conference playoff race.
headlines.shortLinkText: Austin Reaves hits 7 3-pointers, Lakers stun Celtics 114-105 without LeBron James, Anthony Davis

events.name: Indiana Pacers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Maybe Jalen Brunson was just bothered by the pain in his left eye that had been hit a few minutes earlier.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 40 after earning All-Star nod to lead Knicks past Pacers 109-105 for 9th straight win

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had 25 points and seven assists and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Memphis Grizzlies 108-101 on Thursday night for their fourth straight victory and 12th in 13 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell has 25 points, Cavaliers beat Grizzlies 108-101 for 4th straight victory

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored a career-high 51 points hours after being selected to his first All-Star Game, helping the Philadelphia 76ers overcome star center Joel Embiid's absence for a 127-124 victory over the Utah Jazz on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: 1st-time All-Star Maxey scores career-high 51 points to help Embiid-less 76ers beat Jazz 127-124
